-- China Machinery Agrees to $229.5 Million Sri Lanka Water Project
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-05-16T16:50:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/china-machinery-agrees-to-229-5-million-sri-lanka-water-project.html
China Machinery Engineering Corp. (1829) , a
Beijing-based builder, signed a $229.5 million contract for a
water-supply project north of the Sri Lanka capital of Colombo,
the company said today in a Hong Kong exchange filing.  The Gampaha, Attanagalla and Minuwangoda project with the
National Water Supply & Drainage Board of Sri Lanka will take
about 36 months to construct, China Machinery said in the
filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
